{{nihongo|'''Ryakunin'''|暦仁|}} was a {{nihongo|[[Japanese era name]]|年号,|''nengō'',|lit. "year name"}} after ''[[Katei]]'' and before ''[[En'ō]].''  This period spanned the years from November 1238 to April 1239.<ref>Nussbaum, Louis-Frédéric. (2005). "''Ryakunin''" in [http://books.google.com/books?id=p2QnPijAEmEC&pg=PA796&dq=  ''Japan encyclopedia'', p. 796;] n.b., Louis-Frédéric is pseudonym of Louis-Frédéric Nussbaum, ''see'' [http://dispatch.opac.ddb.de/DB=4.1/PPN?PPN=128842709 Deutsche Nationalbibliothek Authority File].</ref> The reigning emperor was {{nihongo|[[Emperor Shijō|Shijō]]''-tennō''|四条天皇}}.<ref>Titsingh, Isaac. (1834). [http://books.google.com/books?id=18oNAAAAIAAJ&pg=PP9&dq=nipon+o+dai+itsi+ran#PRA1-PA242,M1  ''Annales des empereurs du Japon'', pp. 242-244;] Varley, H. Paul. (1980). ''Jinnō Shōtōki.'' p. 227.</ref>

==Change of era==
* '''1238''' {{nihongo|''Ryakunin gannen''|暦仁元年}}:  The era name was changed to mark an event or a number of events.  The previous era ended and a new one commenced in ''Katei'' 4.

==Events of the ''Ryakunin'' Era==
* '''1238''' (''Ryakunin 1, 1st month''): Yoritsune leaves Kamakura en route to Miyako, accompanied by Yaskutoki and the troupes of several provinces.  Fujiwara no Yukimitis stays at Kamakura to preserve order in the land.<ref name="t243">Titsingh, [http://books.google.com/books?id=18oNAAAAIAAJ&pg=PP9&dq=nipon+o+dai+itsi+ran#PRA1-PA243,M1 p. 243.]</ref>
* '''1238''' (''Ryakunin 1, 2nd month''): Yoritsune arrives in Miyako and begins to live in his new palace at Rokuhara.<ref name="t244">Titsingh, [http://books.google.com/books?id=18oNAAAAIAAJ&pg=PP9&dq=nipon+o+dai+itsi+ran#PRA1-PA244,M1  p. 244.]</ref>
* '''1238''' (''Ryakunin 1, 10th month''): Yoritsune leaves Miyako to return to Kamakura.<ref name="t244"/>

